headline: Oracle earnings, February CPI, CERAWeek: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton preview several of the biggest market events and economic data that Wall Street will be following next week. Notable companies like Oracle (ORCL), Viking Holdings (VIK), Adobe (ADBE), Dollar General (DG), Docusign (DOCU), and Ulta Beauty (ULTA) will be reporting their latest earnings results throughout the trading week. Economists will be paying extra close attention to February's inflation data, as the Consumer Price Index (CPI) reading will be published on Wednesday, March 12, followed by the Producer Price Index (PPI) on Thursday, March 13. Yahoo Finance will also be providing in-depth coverage and interviews with leading Wall Street experts from S&P Global's annual CERAWeek energy conference. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.
